Environment

Class Board

  • java.lang.Object
    • Environment.Board

  • public class Board
extends java.lang.Object
    Board class represents the board environment itself. It contains the information of the boundaries, squares, rooms and characters as well as how the move through the board. It initializes the board positions with codes of what each square represents on the board (eg.'D' in the 2D array represents the Dining room, 'X' is wall, '67' is corridor). It initializes the rooms and their positions. The board is drawn for the first time when its created.
